		<pb n="1"/>
			<p rend="align(right)"><placeName>New York</placeName> <date>July 4<hi rend="sup">th</hi> &#47; 53</date></p>
			<p>My Dear Friend&#44;</p>
          <p rend="indent(2)">As I see by last Occident the Bible<lb/> is progressing&#44; I wish you to remember <persName>Rehine&#39;s</persName> wish<lb/> that I should have one of the best&#44; I wish such<lb/> binding as my <hi rend="underline">set</hi> if you recollect&#44; also <del>a book</del><lb/> wish to know what a <hi rend="underline">set</hi> of neat small size a<lb/> wit<hi rend="underline">ho</hi>ut d<hi rend="underline">ai</hi>ly&#44; would cost for <persName>Herman</persName>&#44; if you<lb/> have them&#44; also let me know&#44; what the &#8220;Leper &#38; other<lb/> Poems&#8221; cost&#59; I would thank you to make such<lb/> selections as your <hi rend="underline">good</hi> <sic>Judgement</sic> suggests<lb/> of <persName>Miss Aguilar&#39;s</persName> works&#44; I have Jewish Faith&#44; &#38; home<lb/> Influence&#44; the Essays &#38; miscellanies I think perhaps<lb/> would be useful for <persName>Josephine</persName> let me know<lb/> what &#8220;Vale of Ceaders&#8221; and <hi rend="underline">it</hi> will cost with any you think best. <persName>Rehine</persName><lb/> writes I may have what works I like&#44; still<lb/> I do not wish to Tax him Too far&#8212;I wish<lb/> you&#39;d please have my name on outside<lb/> Bible with from &#8220;son <persName>Rehine</persName>&#8221; I have just written<lb/> a letter to our dear Friend <persName>E Moses</persName>&#44; to come on<lb/> with <persName>Mr Block</persName>&#44; whom I expect soon&#44; <persName>Rosalie</persName><lb/> &#38; family spend the summer with <persName>Lucia</persName>&#44; &#40;<sic>untill</sic><lb/> after her marriage&#44; which you no doubt are<lb/> informed of&#8212;<persName>Eleanor</persName> has gone to <placeName>Arkansas</placeName> to<lb/> Cousin <persName><sic>Franzs</sic></persName> <persName>Sarah</persName> is with the rest at <placeName>Quincy</placeName><lb/> <persName>Abraham</persName> &#38; my Husband go in business at <placeName>Memphis</placeName><lb/> do let me know the state of the Jews if you<lb/> know there as I feel reluctant to go out of congregite<add>&#63;</add></p>
		<pb n="2"/>
			<p>have the Shoket &#38;c&#8212;give my love to <persName>Aunt<lb/> Marks</persName> tell her I was up at <persName>Aunt <sic>Beckys</sic></persName><lb/> yesterday Aunty&#39;s 81<hi rend="sup">st</hi> birthday she looks well<lb/> altho&#39; complains of her eyes&#8212;also best regards<lb/> to <persName>Mr Mrs Florence</persName> and <persName>Allen</persName> and all <sic>enquiring</sic><lb/> friends&#8212;I saw the new importation of <persName>Seixas&#39;</persName><lb/> his Father stayed with us in <placeName>Richmond</placeName> he is very <lb/>like him&#8212;write soon&#8212;hope your health<lb/> is better and that I shall soon<lb/> hear a very <hi rend="underline">desirable</hi> piece of news the<lb/> Union of my good friend <persName>Isaac</persName> with some<lb/> amiable girl&#8212;<persName>Mrs David Cohen</persName> and <persName>&#39;Coll<lb/> Cohen</persName> with two daughters have gone to <placeName>Europe</placeName><lb/> all send love&#59; shall we see you here<lb/> soon&#63; good bye your friend ever <persName role="author">Ablock</persName></p>
		<pb n="3"/>
			<p><addressee>Revd Isaac Leeser</addressee></p>
          <p rend="indent(1)"><placeName><hi rend="underline">Philadelphia</hi></placeName></p>
          
